WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.220
The respiratory act comprises four phases.

2
00:00:02.580 --> 00:00:04.260
Therefore, first we learn to...

3
00:00:04.260 --> 00:00:06.780
I am conscious of my respiration,

4
00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.220
and then I am conscious of following my respiration.

5
00:00:11.100 --> 00:00:14.280
First, you bring mindfulness to the respiration.

6
00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:18.580
Within mindfulness, there is also an energy we call concentration.

7
00:00:19.820 --> 00:00:23.520
Because automatically, I must remain attentive for a longer duration.

8
00:00:26.180 --> 00:00:27.400
Attempt to perceive this.

9
00:00:28.071 --> 00:00:32.011
Scientific research indicates that by working at this level,

10
00:00:32.271 --> 00:00:36.531
you develop empathic faculties, compassion, and attention,

11
00:00:37.011 --> 00:00:38.871
far more subtle, which lead to a state of well-being.

12
00:00:39.131 --> 00:00:42.391
What I refer to as joy, when one learns to remain focused on their respiration,

13
00:00:42.591 --> 00:00:45.051
when one learns to follow their respiration,

14
00:00:45.371 --> 00:00:48.911
subsequently, one learns to recognize the body, uniting body and mind,

15
00:00:49.111 --> 00:00:53.631
and then, at the fourth level, one learns to release the body.

16
00:00:53.891 --> 00:00:56.071
Once this is accomplished, we delve into the essence.

17
00:00:56.142 --> 00:01:01.182
The fifth level is to generate a feeling of joy, which is said to originate from the teachings

18
00:01:01.182 --> 00:01:06.482
of the Buddha, who stated, 'I will teach you 16 ways to engender respiration.'

19
00:01:07.042 --> 00:01:12.222
And then, we will perform an exercise that focuses more on the expiratory act,

20
00:01:12.222 --> 00:01:15.382
which is called 'Brah-mari,' the bee's breath.

21
00:01:15.542 --> 00:01:20.982
This has a very interesting faculty on the brain, rapidly inducing a calm state

22
00:01:20.982 --> 00:01:23.722
of the mind and a reduction in stress.

23
00:01:24.213 --> 00:01:28.253
The tongue is the bud of the heart, and the thyroid originates from the tongue.

24
00:01:28.393 --> 00:01:34.333
One speaks with their heart, in fact, but with the frequential, almost energetic, subtlety,

25
00:01:34.473 --> 00:01:35.513
one might say, of the thyroid.

26
00:01:35.713 --> 00:01:38.313
This implies that at a certain point, it is no longer the word itself, but the sound.

27
00:01:38.773 --> 00:01:40.293
It is the frequency you engage with.

28
00:01:40.633 --> 00:01:44.093
I will guide you; we will perform the first five steps, then we will do the Brah-mari,

29
00:01:44.573 --> 00:01:48.993
and then we will release and simply observe a kind of silence within the body.

30
00:01:49.253 --> 00:01:51.333
One will need to produce a sound originating from the posterior pharynx.

31
00:01:52.284 --> 00:01:57.504
Like a bee or a bumblebee ascending, and this sound must rise into the cavity to

32
00:01:57.504 --> 00:01:59.544
culminate at the level of the sinuses.

33
00:01:59.824 --> 00:02:04.964
We will assess the entire cerebral region, extending into the tympanic cavity and sinus cavity.

34
00:02:06.064 --> 00:02:09.464
Frontal, sphenoidal, maxillary, and even temporal.

35
00:02:09.564 --> 00:02:11.304
We will first adopt an upright posture.

36
00:02:11.444 --> 00:02:16.904
When I straighten my back, upon exhalation, I will experience the true physiological effect

37
00:02:16.904 --> 00:02:19.204
of a release on my vagal tone.

38
00:02:20.355 --> 00:02:22.355
this parasympathetic and restorative system.

39
00:02:22.595 --> 00:02:26.515
If I position myself thus, and restrict here, I diminish this capacity.

40
00:02:26.895 --> 00:02:30.415
I experience this state of inspiratory awareness.

41
00:02:30.795 --> 00:02:36.075
Second level, I am very, very attentive to the act of

42
00:02:36.075 --> 00:02:36.735
respiration.

43
00:02:36.935 --> 00:02:40.975
I am aware of the body's movement during the respiratory act.

44
00:02:41.215 --> 00:02:42.775
Fourth level, I relax.

45
00:02:42.935 --> 00:02:46.815
I relax upon exhalation, fully conscious that I am inhaling.

46
00:02:47.155 --> 00:02:48.355
We will perform twelve respirations.

47
00:02:48.426 --> 00:02:53.046
the first two we will perform thus, and the last ten we will perform with the

48
00:02:53.046 --> 00:02:57.026
ears slightly occluded; you will place your fingers over your ears

49
00:02:57.026 --> 00:03:01.126
to facilitate internal integration; you inhale, and during the

50
00:03:01.126 --> 00:03:03.426
expiratory phase, you produce a gentle humming sound.

51
00:03:13.066 --> 00:03:16.426
we inhale, occlude the ears, and you perform this

52
00:03:16.497 --> 00:03:22.677
ten times, and then you may release; you

53
00:03:22.677 --> 00:03:26.777
enter into the emerging silence, and within this silence, you

54
00:03:26.777 --> 00:03:32.537
simply allow a feeling of joy to arise, and

55
00:03:32.537 --> 00:03:34.837
if you are unsure what to do, offer a small

56
00:03:34.837 --> 00:03:41.457
smile; take another inhalation, perform

57
00:03:41.457 --> 00:03:43.857
an exhalation, and at the conclusion of the exhalation,

58
00:03:44.568 --> 00:03:47.088
There is a space where you do not respire.

59
00:03:48.528 --> 00:03:50.248
But you settle your consciousness within this space.

60
00:03:52.848 --> 00:03:55.388
Even as you reinspire, you remain within this space.

61
00:03:56.868 --> 00:04:02.288
When you enter this perception, you bring yourself closer

62
00:04:02.288 --> 00:04:04.168
to the embryonic breath.

63
00:04:05.368 --> 00:04:09.128
Because the embryonic breath was not subject to diaphragmatic movements.

64
00:04:10.228 --> 00:04:12.508
And if you do so, you will begin

65
00:04:12.639 --> 00:04:17.719
to perceive your heart, which was there eight months

66
00:04:17.719 --> 00:04:22.419
and nine days before your thoracic respiration.

67
00:04:23.799 --> 00:04:28.239
In other words, your heart begins to beat after 21 days.

68
00:04:29.319 --> 00:04:32.579
And so it is good to place oneself, from time to time, in this silence,

69
00:04:32.759 --> 00:04:35.179
because it is in silence that reorganization can occur.

70
00:04:35.639 --> 00:04:39.739
This embryonic force is always present, but to enter into

71
00:04:39.739 --> 00:04:40.459
this presence,

72
00:04:40.710 --> 00:04:45.730
this contact, you must accept to go into silence. You might rediscover

73
00:04:45.730 --> 00:04:46.930
a healing movement. Or that health can express itself, flourish more

74
00:04:46.930 --> 00:04:51.950
easily.

75
00:04:51.950 --> 00:04:52.470
You place it in this silence and allow space to open. Thus, a need for space.

76
00:04:53.470 --> 00:04:58.330
If there is no space, there is no development. Therefore, both this

77
00:04:59.310 --> 00:05:03.910
spacious silence are required. But if you restore to the tissue this

78
00:05:03.910 --> 00:05:08.710
capacity

79
00:05:08.781 --> 00:05:09.561
to rediscover this moment of silence,

80
00:05:10.341 --> 00:05:11.961
the body knows very well how it should reorganize itself because

81
00:05:12.621 --> 00:05:16.501
there it can utilize

82
00:05:16.501 --> 00:05:17.321
its potential upon which it was created.

83
00:05:17.321 --> 00:05:19.541
Therefore, I restore the possibility to the system that it knows,

84
00:05:20.221 --> 00:05:24.301
but it is so occupied that it no longer knows.

85
00:05:24.961 --> 00:05:26.801
I restore this vital principle.

86
00:05:27.721 --> 00:05:29.401
je redonne ce principe vital

